On Leif Erikson Day, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation to celebrate the journey made by Leif Erikson, who is believed to be the first European to reach North America over a millennium ago. The proclamation recognizes the contributions of Nordic Americans to the United States, highlighting their achievements in various fields such as science, engineering, arts, and military service. It also emphasizes the strong ties and partnerships between the United States and the Nordic countries. The proclamation concludes by declaring October 9, 2018, as Leif Erikson Day and calling upon Americans to celebrate Nordic American heritage.